right to the point then.

01:30:12.443 --> 01:30:14.235
I don't think you oughta go.

01:30:14.403 --> 01:30:18.239
I think I made a big mistake.
And I would prefer it if you didn't go.

01:30:18.407 --> 01:30:20.408
Oh, Isaac.

01:30:20.576 --> 01:30:24.954
I mean it. I know it looks real bad now,
but, uh, you know, it, uh...

01:30:25.122 --> 01:30:27.999
Are you seeing anybody?
Are you going with anybody?

01:30:28.167 --> 01:30:29.625
No.

01:30:30.711 --> 01:30:32.712
So... well...

01:30:32.880 --> 01:30:36.841
D'you still love me,
or has that worn off or what?

01:30:38.552 --> 01:30:40.636
Jesus, you... pop up...

01:30:41.555 --> 01:30:44.641
You don't call me
and then you suddenly appear.

01:30:45.226 --> 01:30:48.854
I mean... What happened
to that woman you met?

01:30:49.022 --> 01:30:52.691
Well, I'll tell you,
I don't see her any more.

01:30:52.859 --> 01:30:56.612
I made a mistake.
What d'you want me to say?

01:30:57.614 --> 01:31:00.115
I don't think you oughta go to London.

01:31:02.786 --> 01:31:04.953
Well, I have to go.

01:31:05.121 --> 01:31:07.915
I mean, all the plans
have been made, arrangements.

01:31:08.083 --> 01:31:12.503
I mean, my parents are there now
looking for a place for me to live.

01:31:14.506 --> 01:31:16.507
Well...

01:31:16.674 --> 01:31:19.593
Do you still love me or what?

01:31:21.054 --> 01:31:23.138
Do you love me?

01:31:23.640 --> 01:31:26.058
Well, yeah, that's what... Of course.

01:31:26.226 --> 01:31:28.852
That's what this is all about, you know.

01:31:29.020 --> 01:31:31.772
- Guess what? I turned 18 the other day.
- Did you?

01:31:31.940 --> 01:31:34.108
I'm legal, but I'm still a kid.

01:31:34.275 --> 01:31:37.277
You're not such a kid. 18 years old.

01:31:37.445 --> 01:31:40.782
They could draft you.
In some countries you'd be...

01:31:43.452 --> 01:31:46.704
- You look good.
- You really hurt me.

01:31:46.872 --> 01:31:48.915
It was not on purpose, you know.

01:31:49.083 --> 01:31:52.419
I mean, I, uh...
You know, it was... I mean...

01:31:53.254 --> 01:31:56.172
It was just the way
I was looking at things then.

01:31:56.340 --> 01:31:58.842
Well, I'll be back in six months.

01:31:59.009 --> 01:32:01.511
Six months! Are you kidding?

01:32:02.179 --> 01:32:04.472
Six months you're gonna go for?

01:32:05.641 --> 01:32:11.020
We've gone this long. I mean, what's
six months if we still love each other?

01:32:11.188 --> 01:32:13.189
Hey, don't be so mature, OK?

01:32:13.357 --> 01:32:15.984
I mean, six months is a long time.
Six months!

01:32:16.152 --> 01:32:19.404
You're gonna be in the thea...

01:32:19.572 --> 01:32:21.823
...working in the theatre
with actors and directors.

01:32:21.991 --> 01:32:25.785
You know, you go to rehearsal
and you hang out with those people.

01:32:25.953 --> 01:32:31.499
You have lunch a lot and before you know
it attachments form and... you know...

01:32:31.667 --> 01:32:35.336
I mean, you don't wanna get into that...
You'll change.

01:32:35.504 --> 01:32:38.549
In six months you'll be
a completely different person.

01:32:38.717 --> 01:32:41.927
Well, don't you want me
to have that experience?

01:32:42.095 --> 01:32:45.347
I mean, a while ago
you made such a convincing case.

01:32:47.392 --> 01:32:50.644
Yeah, of course I do, but, you know...

01:32:50.812 --> 01:32:55.191
I mean, I just don't want that thing
about you that I like to change.

01:32:59.571 --> 01:33:01.697
I've gotta make a plane.

01:33:01.865 --> 01:33:04.783
Come on, you don't... Come on.

01:33:04.951 --> 01:33:07.369
You don't... You don't have to go.

01:33:08.371 --> 01:33:11.707
Why couldn't you have
brought this up last week?

01:33:14.377 --> 01:33:16.795
Six months isn't so long.

01:33:18.548 --> 01:33:21.050
Not everybody gets corrupted.

01:33:23.271 --> 01:33:26.639
You have to have
a little faith in people.

